{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give State Pension to all at 60 and increase it to equal 48hrs at Living Wage",
        "additional_details": "Hence from April 2024, a universal State Pension should be \u00a3549.12 per week or about \u00a328,554.24 per year as a right to all including expatriates, age 60 and above.\r\n\r\nWe think that Government policy seems intent on the State Pension being a benefit, while increasing the age of entitlement. We want reforms so the State Pension is available from age 60, and linked to the National Living Wage.",
        "background": "We want the Government to make the State Pension available from the age of 60 and increase this to equal 48 hours a week at the National Living Wage.",
